      <section class="open-letter-zone" id="open-letter">
        <div class="shell">
          <div class="open-letter">
            <div class="letter-header">
              <p class="letter-type">An Open Memorandum</p>
              <div class="letter-meta">
                <p><strong>Date:</strong> May 2026</p>
                <p><strong>To:</strong> The Honorable Governor of Uttar Pradesh / Chancellor of State Universities</p>
                <p><strong>From:</strong> The United Student Body of Uttar Pradesh Colleges</p>
                <p><strong>Subject:</strong> Appeal Against the Mandating of Standardized Uniform Dress Codes</p>
              </div>
            </div>
            <div class="letter-body">
              <p>Respected Governor,</p>
              <p>We write to you as adult citizens, voters, and scholars of this state. The recent directive mandating standardized uniforms across all state universities and colleges fundamentally misunderstands what higher education is meant to be.</p>
              <p>A university is a sanctuary for critical inquiry, diverse perspectives, and professional growth — not a parade ground. By compelling adult students to adhere to school-level dress codes, the state diminishes our personal agency and signals that conformity matters more than competence. This policy also imposes real economic and logistical hardship on hostel residents, who now face daily laundry cycles under threat of academic penalty.</p>
              <p>We urge you to reconsider. Invest in laboratories, libraries, and placements — not in policing what adult scholars wear.</p>
            </div>
          </div>
        </div>
      </section>

