      <section class="manifesto" id="manifesto">
        <div class="shell">
          <p class="section-kicker">The Argument</p>
          <h2>Why Uniform Is Not A Good Idea</h2>
          <p class="manifesto-intro">
            University is not school. A uniform policy ignores that students are adults with
            distinct identities, constrained budgets, and a right to self-expression.
          </p>

          <ol class="demand-grid">
            <li class="demand-item">
              <div class="demand-title">
                <h3>Recognition of Autonomy</h3>
              </div>
              <p>
                University students are legal adults, voters, and independent thinkers. Dictating
                adult attire infantilizes higher education and suppresses individuality.
              </p>
            </li>

            <li class="demand-item">
              <div class="demand-title">
                <h3>Expression &amp; Diversity</h3>
              </div>
              <p>
                Higher education thrives on personal and intellectual diversity. A standardized
                uniform dress code sanitizes individual identity and suppresses creative
                self-expression, reducing vibrant academic institutions to rigid assembly lines.
                Students from diverse cultural and economic backgrounds express their identity
                through attire — a uniform erases that richness.
              </p>
            </li>

            <li class="demand-item">
              <div class="demand-title">
                <h3>Overhead Cost of the Hostel</h3>
              </div>
              <p>
                Hostel students manage limited laundry facilities and demanding academic schedules.
                Mandating daily uniform washing cycles under threat of academic penalties creates
                unnecessary financial strain and day-to-day stress, detracting from core academic
                performance.
              </p>
            </li>

            <li class="demand-item">
              <div class="demand-title">
                <h3>Focus on Excellence, Not Apparel</h3>
              </div>
              <p>
                Discipline in universities is built through academic rigor, research, and critical
                thinking. Administration must prioritize infrastructure and placements, not policing
                wardrobes.
              </p>
            </li>
          </ol>
        </div>
      </section>

